CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 28, 1949, reads: "Auto Club Guests - Edward Russ, Eugene Dozzi and John Gaines, left to right, are pictured above after their recent trip to Washington, D.C., as guests of the Wilkinsburg Auto Club. The boys were representing the Lincoln Park Junior High School and marched in national Safety Council's parade.  John is captain of the Lincoln patrol and also president of his class of which Edward is secretary. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of three Lincoln Park Junior High School safety patrol members, from left: Edward Russ, Eugene Dozzi and John Gaines, wearing light colored sashes, standing in front of grassy field with brick building in background with "Coca cola" sign over doorway
